PAT is an auto test tool for power test

1.PAT environment setup
    1).change work dir to "PAT".
    2).run ./install_ppat.sh, maybe this need sudo permission.

2.Prepare for run PAT
    1).setup board, install some test apk, events. Plug in usb, run prepare_ppat.sh 
    2).after prepare_ppat.sh finished, plug out usb

3.Run PAT
    1). list all available test cases
    run "python startppat.py listall"
    then, get output:
        [ListAllCases] caseID       caseName
        [ListAllCases]  0       Audio_Record
        [ListAllCases]  1       FM
        [ListAllCases]  2       mp3
        [ListAllCases]  3       standby
        [ListAllCases]  4       home

    2). run case, for example run home for eden
    run "python startppat.py --platform=eden --ser-port=USB0 --tc-list=4"
    
    3).round pp table 
    If you need round pp table, for example: 
    Fix CPU: 1 core, 624MHz
        DDR: 104MHz, 156MHz
        GPU0: 208MHz
        GPU1: 156MHz
        VPU0: 416MHz
        VPU1: 416MHz
    then, if run those pp for eden video 1080p case, create case/basic/power/video/1080p/precondition.eden.xml, the content is:

	<?xml version="1.0"?>
	<project basedir="." default="run">
    	<include file="${user.dir}/config/command.xml"/>
		<target name="run">
			<RoundPP>
				<ddr>
                 	<Frequency>104000,156000</Frequency>
                </ddr>
                <vpu>
            	    <unit id="0">
            	        <Frequency>416000</Frequency>
                    </unit>
                    <unit id="1">
                        <Frequency>416000</Frequency>
                    </unit>
                </vpu>
                <gpu>
                    <unit id="0">
            	        <Frequency>208000</Frequency>
                    </unit>
                    <unit id="1">
            	        <Frequency>156000</Frequency>
                    </unit>
                </gpu>
                <cpu>
                    <CoreNum>1</CoreNum>
                    <Frequency>624000</Frequency>
                </cpu>
			</RoundPP>
		</target>
	</project>    	

     then, run "python startppat.py --platform=eden --ser-port=USB0 --tc-list=1080p"

 NOTE:
    Every time finish this test, precondition.eden.xml will be move the "resoult" folder.
    If you need create or move this xml file to case/basic/power/video/1080p/ folder

4.get result
    after finished, in "result" folder will generate a folder named with PAT running time, in that folder "Power_Result.html" is the final result


note(ubuntu linux): 
serial port you need to addgroup to "dialout"
1.run command: groups $USER
    $ groups $USER
    mamh : mamh adm tty dialout fax cdrom floppy tape sudo dip video plugdev fuse lpadmin admin nopasswdlogin sambashare vboxusers
2.if your user not in group dialout, please run command(this need sudo permission): sudo adduser $USER dialout
